&lt;h1 id="the-cutting-edge"&gt;The Cutting Edge&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Edge AI doesn&amp;rsquo;t have to live in the cloud when it can live on you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The badge runs inference directly on a $3 microcontroller, and we want to work with hardware vendors like you to bring new demos and capabilities to life!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>London 2026: Launching the First Badges!</title><link>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/blog/london-2026-launching-the-first-badges/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/blog/london-2026-launching-the-first-badges/</guid><description>Coming soon.</description></item><item><title>Add Secure Boot to Any Project</title><link>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/blog/add-secure-boot-to-any-project/</link><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/blog/add-secure-boot-to-any-project/</guid><description>Using OPTIGA-TRUST-M to make any microcontroller project secure for IoT.</description></item><item><title>Overview</title><link>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/hardware/overview/</link><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://lyndlabs.github.io/Edge-AI-Badge-Docs/hardware/overview/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout-note d-flex flex-row mt-4 mb-4 pt-4 pe-4 pb-2 ps-3"&gt;
 
